  "eprint": {
    "title": "Feather: Lightweight Multi-party Updatable Delegated Private Set Intersection",
    "authors": [
      {
        "name": "Aydin Abadi",
        "email": "abadi@ed",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Sotirios Terzis",
        "email": "",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Changyu Dong",
        "email": "",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "Abstract. With the growth of cloud computing, the need arises for Private Set Intersection (PSI) protocols\nthat can operate on outsourced data and delegate computation to cloud servers. One limitation of\nexisting delegated PSI protocols is that they are all designed for static data and do not allow efficient\nupdate on outsourced data. Another limitation is that they cannot efficiently support PSI among multiple\nclients, which is often needed in practice. This paper presents “Feather”, the first delegated PSI protocol\nthat supports efficient data updates and scalable multi-party PSI computation on outsourced datasets.\nIt lets clients independently prepare and upload their private data to the cloud once, then delegate the\ncomputation an unlimited number of times. The update operation has very low communication and\ncomputation complexity, and this is achieved without sacrificing PSI efficiency and security. Feather\ndoes not use public key cryptography, that makes it more scalable. We have implemented a prototype\nand compared the concrete performance against the state of the art. The evaluation indicates that Feather\ndoes achieve better performance in both update and PSI computation.",
    "keywords": [
      "Private Set Intersection",
      "Cloud Computing",
      "Cryptographic Protocols",
      "Multi-party Computation"
    ],
    "category": "Cryptographic protocols",
    "publication_info": "Preprint. MINOR revision.",
    "last_updated": "2021-01-06",
